title: Arresting finale to festival
text:
Cairns’ Tropical Mardi Gras grows from strength to strength by: What are these? Senior Constable Jess Porter and Police Liason Officer Pepsi Li complete a fake arrest of Marina Mirage at the Tropical Mardi Gras family fair day at the Tanks. PICTURE: JUSTIN BRIERTY Source: News Limited 
AFTER 11 days of festivities, Cairns’ 2015 Tropical Mardi Gras finished in fine style at the Tanks yesterday. Mark Mills at the Tropical Mardi Gras family fair day at the Tanks. PICTURE: JUSTIN BRIERTY Source: News Limited 
Festival spokesman Andrew Wheatland said the event had grown to become a highlight on the local entertainment calender. 
“It’s a great way for the wider community to celebrate the contribution of gay and lesbian people to the Far North,” he said. 
A Mardi Gras art exhibition will remain on display at the Tanks until October 31. Di Queen and Victor Francioni at the Tropical Mardi Gras family fair day at the Tanks. PICTURE: JUSTIN BRIERTY Source: News Limited
